Why I became an egg donor - Tulip Skip to content Start My Search How Tulip Works Education & Resources Log In Sign Up Show Menu Close Menu Start My Search How Tulip Works Education & Resources Log In Sign Up Why I became an egg donor Written by Nina McCullough Posted in The Process Updated 2 months ago Egg donation isn’t for It takes a special person to go through the physical and emotional journey of being an egg donor, and there are a lot of myths around egg Do they only do it for the money? Is it painful? Can anyone be an egg donor? We asked Amber to share her experience and answer all your questions! Why would you choose to be an egg donor? Amber: I heard of a friend donating to a local clinic about 5 years before I actually decided to It wasn’t until several years later that I was faced with the idea that I might not be able to have children with my In a specialist waiting room, I was reintroduced to egg I understood donation on a completely different If there was someone out there who could help ME have children, wouldn’t giving that gift in return be a beautiful thing? Do egg donors only donate for the money? Amber: Egg donation can be an incredibly fulfilling and rewarding process, with or without Being selected as an egg donor was an incredibly emotional experience for me and other donors I’ve talked to had similar Many donors come to egg donation after seeing a loved one go through the struggle of infertility and wanting to help someone else going through the same But compensation definitely helps, and I think it’s justified since these young women are committing a significant amount of time and effort to Can anyone be an egg donor? Amber: No – there is a fairly rigorous vetting process before you can become an egg You typically apply to a clinic or agency who ask you about your basic Your answers about your health history may disqualify Then you answer a more thorough questionnaire and describe yourself, your family, and your family’s health If the preliminary review of your profile passes the requirements set forth by ASRM, you are able to create a If you match with a couple, you undergo genetic testing to ensure compatibility with the Donors must also undergo ovarian reserve and hormone level testing, psychological screenings, genetic counseling, FDA screenings, and drug and nicotine Is egg donation really painful dangerous? Amber: Egg donation is a surgical procedure, so it should be taken I’ve seen donors who are concerned about the hormone injections, but for me they were The surgical procedure to retrieve eggs took about minutes, and I had some mild cramps There are potential side effects that you need to be aware of as you go through the donation process, but clinics monitor donors closely to make sure they are safe and Were you scared of donating impacting your own fertility? Amber: I see this question all the time, and it was a concern of mine as well when I was thinking about As far as I’ve seen, there is no evidence to support claims that donating eggs will harm future Since donating, I’ve had two healthy children of my own, so it definitely wasn’t an issue for Is it difficult to take time off of school or work? Amber: For me it wasn’t, but it depends on the situation! Egg donors can choose to donate with a clinic nearby, so travel wouldn’t be If you cycle with an agency, then there is a higher chance you might travel to the intended parents’ clinic, but you choose whether or not you’re willing to do a travel If you agree to match with a couple that isn’t in your area, you might travel around days total for your screening, injection training, and then your Did you tell anyone? What did your family and friends think of you being an egg donor? Amber: I told my family I was My husband was very The rest of my family had questions and confusion – they didn’t really understand how egg donation works – but they were supportive of my I’ve never regretted my decision to donate, and my family now is just happy that my participation brought happiness to someone else’s Amber’s name has been changed to protect her Share this post: Twitter Facebook Pinterest LinkedIn Email Post navigation Previous Post Previous How to talk to kids about egg donation Next Post Next Our story Topic Search To search this site, enter a search term Follow Tulip Categories Expert Opinions The Process Tulip Talk Start My Search How Tulip Works Education & Resources Log In Sign Up Contact Us Terms & Conditions Privacy Policy © Tulip × Contact us Name Phone Email Message Captcha are required fields Upgrade to concierge level membership × For additional support and personalized, service, try Donor Concierge At the concierge level, our team of expert case managers curate a list of available donors for you and liaise with the agencies on your We help you find the right match quickly - usually within weeks - enabling you to begin your egg donor cycle Learn More Return To Tulip First Name Last Name Email Address Contact Number

If you have been hurt on the job, you need someone to help you recover and look after your best Your injury may keep you from Workers’ Compensation Law allows workers who get hurt in accidents to receive compensation for their medical bills and lost Most employers are required to purchase workers compensation insurance to cover employees in the event of an As long as the employee suffered a type of injury covered by the Workers Compensation Act, he or she can make a claim and receive The law may be complicated and difficult to The law requires employees to immediately notify their employers and provides a short window of time to make a Some employers try to discourage workers from filing a Worker’s Compensation claim, but do not Insurance companies deny many claims if the employee delays reporting and filing a Employers cannot legally fire you for making a Workers’ Compensation Instead of taking this risk, consult an experienced The Law Offices of Stefan Latorre can help you through this process and make sure you receive the medical treatment and compensation you We offer a free initial consultation and you will pay no legal fees until we recover a compensation for Why do you need an attorney? There is a complex legal process involved in making a claim for a workers’ compensation An experienced workers’ compensation attorney can help ensure you get the medical treatment you need and obtain the best possible Insurance companies have experienced adjusters and attorneys that will attempt to resolve claims for their Without an attorney you may end up with less than you For this reason, you should also have an experienced attorney representing you and ensuring you obtain the best settlement for your An experience attorney can also review your case and inform you whether you might have a claim against someone other than your In addition, if you are concerned with discrimination because of a workers’ compensation claim, an attorney can protect your rights and make sure your employer is complying with the If you have been injured at work, time is of the essence! The longer you wait to make your claim, the more likely the insurance company will deny it causing further delay in obtaining your compensation or medical Why Us? At The Law Offices of Stefan Latorre we are committed to helping injured Our team of experienced and dedicated personal injury attorneys and legal professionals has helped thousands of injured people and their families throughout the Carolinas and We understand the legal system and how insurance companies We work diligently to obtain acceptance of a claim so our clients can receive medical attention and disability checks throughout their recovery and often until settlement of the We pride ourselves if providing aggressive legal representation in order to obtain the best results and compensation for our We do not believe that a person’s wealth, education, or legal status should have anything to do with their right to We offer a free initial consultation and we charge no legal fees until we recover a compensation for Stefan Latorre has successfully argued many cases, but he is most proud of two precedent setting In the case of Francisco Ruiz Belk Masonry , the North Carolina Court of Appeals established the right to workers’ compensation benefits for injured workers regardless of their immigration Prior to this case, undocumented workers were routinely denied workers’ compensation benefits solely because of their lack of legal This case seminal case, made it possible for all injured undocumented workers to receive workers’ compensation benefits in North Latorre also successfully argued the case of Vicente Acosta Edwin Painting , where the Industrial Commission in a case of first impression determined that an injured worker who was not fluent in the English language was entitled to an interpreter for all medical Prior to this case, insurance companies refused to provide interpreters for some medical appointments, thus depriving them of the To move to the cloud, companies are using various methods to provision and deploy That includes custom built scripts, manual provisioning from interfaces, use of available provisioning engines and use of custom automation Since the deployed resources in the cloud could grow exponentially over the time, the Security Operators (SecOps) team should be equipped with the right tools to ensure cloud Prancer is a validation framework which can be used by any company Security Operators to validate and verify cloud implementation before and after the This and validation framework can connect to multiple cloud providers including Microsoft Azure, Amazon AWS and Google cloud to validate the resources you have deployed in the (Note: other cloud providers are in development: Oracle, VMWare, Cloud Foundation, ) Prancer engine has the capability to read out the configuration attributes from any parameter file or automation framework and use it as a blueprint to compare to the configuration values you have in your cloud It can read out the values from your cloud provisioning engine and compare it to the deployed resources to validate the implementation and find out any configuration Prancer cloud validation framework is equipped with industry compliance tests (HIPPA, PCI, SCI,etc,) to automatically initiate a compliance scan of your infrastructure as code (IaC) and cloud deployed resources to make sure you are in for more information you can check the website: https: www.prancer.io prerequisites Linux based OS Python mongo database Note: mongo database is not a hard requirement to run prancer cloud validation It is possible to run the framework and write all the outputs to the file To learn more, you can review prancer documentations prancer installation Clone the cloud validation framework repository at https: github.com prancer-io cloud-validation-framework.git cd Install the dependent packages as present in pip3 install [optional] Install mongo server and start the (The mongoDB could be local or remote and you can set it in file "dburl") [optional] Update to reflect the database server export the following variables: export BASEDIR=`pwd` export PYTHONPATH=$BASEDIR src export FRAMEWORKDIR=$BASEDIR Run the tests from the filesystem: python3 utilities validator.py <arguments About prancer cloud validation framework is a validation engine to have any questions, call We’re here to listen, About Title Insurance Title policies insure owners and lenders against possible losses from claims against real property The preliminary report or commitment provides advance information on coverage Lenders and owners are thereby given an opportunity to correct title flaws before purchasing or Title insurance originated in the to stem land ownership problems caused by inaccurate record searches, forgeries, and related Today, title insurance offers protection from certain items that cannot be determined from public records, items including forgeries, undisclosed heirs, hidden marriages and divorces, clerical errors, and invalid legal procedures and Policies are written on the basis of a search of public records and other records that impart constructive Remember: A deed does not prove that the seller is the owner of the property only title insurance can protect your interest in the property from unknown encumbrances, legal conflicts, and unforeseen A title insurance policy is like a prepaid legal Your insurer will provide legal defense against challenges to your insured title (depending on the type of policy coverage) and will reimburse you financially for losses due to the covered defects in your ownership It’s important to remember that a lender’s title policy does not insure a borrower against title While certain types of policies pertain to both the owner and the lender, it makes good sense to help protect your borrowers by explaining the limitations of their particular The following sections explain the most common policies and endorsements used If you have any questions about which works best in any particular situation, give us a American Land Title Association (ALTA) Policy In most jurisdictions, the ALTA Extended Coverage loan policy is the most common policy offering extended coverage for the lender’s interest This means the lender is protected from certain additional “off-record” matters such as encroachments, unrecorded eas

Color - Small About Us Resources Media News Press Releases Contact About Us Autonomous vehicle technology will create opportunities and challenges for American Together, the Partnership for Transportation Innovation and Opportunity will find solutions that ensure Americans can benefit from adoption of this The Partnership for Transportation Innovation and Opportunity was formed by leading companies and associations committed to advancing autonomous vehicle technology in ways that improve quality of life and economic opportunity for all Led by our partners at the American Trucking Associations, Daimler, FedEx, Ford, Lyft, Toyota Motor North America, UPS, and Waymo, our mission is to promote open and thorough discourse through a robust educational campaign to determine the opportunities and challenges autonomous vehicles may create for American We will also focus on the role public policy can play in helping our entire workforce benefit from the adoption of autonomous vehicle Together with impacted communities, stakeholders, and policymakers, we will work to address the employment impacts this technology may make . PTIO – a coalition led by the American Trucking Associations, Daimler, FedEx, Ford, Lyft, Toyota Motor North America, UPS, and Waymo – is committed to advancing autonomous vehicle technology in ways that improve quality of life and economic opportunity for all PTIO launched in June to prepare American workers for autonomous vehicles and to examine the impact the technology could have on the future of Prior to her role with PTIO, Kathryn spent time on Capitol Hill working on a wide array of issues, including labor and employment, education, technology, and healthcare Our Principles Innovation We support innovation in the transportation sector through the introduction of autonomous vehicles, and encourage policies that enable autonomous vehicles to flourish, while prioritizing We value the societal benefits that autonomous vehicles will deliver through safety, environmental, and economic We acknowledge that autonomous vehicles will also change the future of work and enable new career pathways that will be integral to century Transparency We will engage in open and honest communication with policymakers and impacted communities about autonomous vehicles and the new business models they will We will partner with other stakeholders willing to promote this important Knowledge W

No Phone Calls Made With ringless voicemail, there is no The telemarketer directly loads the word into the customerâs voicemail This push voicemail service is noninvasive to customers, and marketers donât have to sit and wait for the phone to It Works With TCPA Regulations Ringless voicemail is a gold mine of conversion opportunities for small and large businesses Unlike in cold calling where you can be slapped with a TCPA lawsuit (Telephone Consumer Protection Act), placing a voicemail into a customerâs phone without it ringing is compliant with federal laws because no real calls are made and thus classified under the TCPA as an “Enhanced Service” The Message Gets Home With Ease When you implement ringless voicemail, you get to send your brand message to customers with You donât have to call your customers, or sit and wait for them to answer hoping that they donât hang up in the middle of the You only have to record the message and send the The Message Gets Home At The Right Time A message is better than a phone call communication teaches us The good thing with a voice mail message is that a customer will listen to it at their If during the middle of the day a customer would have hung up because they were busy, they can comfortably listen to your voicemail message after five during or during a lunch They can also play it over and over again, or refer back to it at a later You Cover More Marketing Ground Ringless voicemail can enable you to reach a wider audience within a short You get to cut down on marketing costs since recording and pushing voicemail messages is a task that can be accomplished by one Dial Back Option for Customers When the customer receives your voicemail, your phone number will show as the caller ID . Adaptogens are the wellness industry’s latest buzzword - adaptogenic lattes are popping up in salad bars and blends are finding their home on the shelves of Some adaptogens like ashwagandha, can be taken in a powdered While others, like Lion’s Mane mushroom, can be a nice dinnertime side So, what are they? Adaptogens are a category of herbs and mushrooms that help balance your body’s reaction to stress by modulating it’s hormonal and physiological Adaptogens improve adrenal function, protect you from disease, boost immune function and improve overall [1]. Brenda Powell, director of the Center for Integrative and Lifestyle Medicine at the Cleveland Clinic’s Wellness Institute, says that “adaptogens help your body handle They’re meant to bring us back to the ” [2] Herbs and mushrooms such as reishi mushroom, ashwagandha, and eleuthero root have been used for centuries by Traditional Chinese Medicine and Aruveydic healing traditions for their adaptogenic “adaptogens help your body handle They’re meant to bring us back to the ” - Brenda Powell, Center for Integrative and Lifestyle Medidine, Cleveland Clinic Wellness Institute In order to be defined as an adaptogen, an herb or mushroom must meet the following criteria: Help the body resist a stress response in a way + help the body resist a broad spectrum of This can include physical, chemical, or biological Let’s say you’re a famous sprinter, like Usain Bolt, and you spend several hours training every single While exercising, lactic acid builds up in your muscles, causing muscle fatigue and muscle soreness - so you might not exercise for as long as you But if you take an adaptogen like cordyceps sinensis, you may be able to delay that muscle fatigue because your body would experience enhanced oxygen utilization and blood flow (i.e the lactic acid is cleared from your muscles quicker) [3] . Not to mention your body will be feeling all sorts of other effects like enhanced immune regulation and less inflammation [4] . So, while cordyceps can help with physical stressors like muscle fatigue, it can also help with biological stressors by enhancing immune See how adaptogens can be? Maintain homeostasis in Not familiar with the term ‘homeostasis’? Not a Homeostasis means keeping the body at a relatively steady For instance, if you start a new job where you have to go to long, stressful meetings and you don’t get much sleep as you should, you’ll find that your adrenal gland is secreting a lot more cortisol than it used In other words, you’re stressed out! Starting that new job has knocked you out of equilibrium and, as a person with sudden external stress, you are more susceptible to disorders such as gastric ulcers, weight gain, and To qualify as an adaptogen, an herb or mushroom must help your body resist disorders like Must not harm the An adaptogen cannot have any side effects, or do anything that might mess with your body’s normal Further Reading + References: What Are Adaptogens and Why Are People Taking Them? (Time Magazine) What Are Adaptogens? (New York Times) What Are Adaptogens? (Greatist) Types of Adaptogens Yance, an herbal doctor who wrote a book entitled “Adaptogens in Medical Herbalism,” divided adaptogens into three categories based on his clinical experience: primary adaptogens, secondary adaptogens, and adaptogen companions [5] . Primary Adaptogens satisfy all 3 requirements needed to be an In other words, there is abundant scientific research confirming their adaptogenic properties such as the ability to help the body resist a stress response in a way and the ability to help the body maintain Primary adaptogens directly influence the (HPA) axis in response to Haven’t heard of the HPA axis? Don’t worry, we will go into that Just know for now that primary adaptogens can influence it Secondary Adaptogens meet the traditional definition of being an adaptogen but don’t quite meet all three Unlike primary adaptogens, they don’t influence the HPA axis However, they do influence the nervous, endocrine, and immune They also don’t have as extensive of scientific studies backing their properties as primary Adaptogen Companions don’t satisfy all of the traditional rules to actually be an adaptogen, but they do have positive effects on the HPA axis and work to support the functions of primary and secondary In other words, adaptogen companions work synergistically with adaptogens in order to improve the effects that they Ok, now what’s the (HPA) Axis? Getting started with genetic testing - Genetics - Gene Food Menu Search for: Search Custom Nutrition ecoHome Resources DNA Recipes Genetics Genetics and Nutrition Guide Science Score About Aaron Gardner John O’Connor Danielle Moore Leigh Matthews Blog Contact Search for: Search Home » Genetics Genetics Before we get into the science, here’s a refresher on the language used to describe and discuss all things genetics, as well as the resources we recommend to get started on your nutrigenomic Getting started You can learn your genotype for all of the genes listed in our Guide to Nutrigenomics by ordering a test kit from (you’ll want Health and Ancestry). From there, we recommend Amy Yasko’s book, Feel Good Nutrigenomics , as a good resource to begin learning how your genetics should influence Now on to Genetics , and everything about genes you forgot from high The code within your cells Our body is made up of roughly trillion cells, all with specialized functions, creating the diverse range of tissues and organs required to make a Within each cell, in a structure known as the nucleus , we have pairs of chromosomes (hence the name of ), which is chromosomes in These pairs of chromosomes are inherited from your parents, one from your mother and one from your The sex chromosome pair determine whether you are male (XY) or female (XX). While the other pairs of chromosomes are known as autosomes . Each chromosome is composed of tightly packed chromatin this is a structure made up of DNA (deoxyribonucleic acids), wrapped around proteins known as The DNA molecule consists of two strands which wind around each other to form a double helix ‘twisted ladder’ The sides of the ladder are made up of sugars and phosphates while the ‘rungs’ of the DNA ladder are pairs of nucleic acids, known as base pairs . There are four types of bases in DNA adenine (A), thymine (T), cytosine (C) and guanine (G). The bases pair in a specific way A always pairs with T, and C always pairs with So how does DNA provide the instructions to make us? The genetic code is formed from the bases along one strand of the DNA molecule, known as the DNA The DNA sequence is broken up into genes , units of the DNA sequence which provide the instructions for making The complete set of human DNA (3 billion base pairs!), including all genes, is known as the genome . The bases A, T, C and G are the ‘letters’ of the DNA sequence, with each group of three letters forming a ‘word’ known as a Each codon is associated with a specific amino acid , as the codons are ‘read’ along the DNA strand, the specific amino acid is added to a growing chain which, once complete, forms a Proteins are the building blocks of life they form the components of every one of those trillion cells as well as acting in a whole host of processes that keep us Patterns of Inheritance As we have previously discussed, we inherit half our genetic code from our mother and half from our Therefore, at every position in our genome we have two alleles (forms of the gene), one inherited from each The genotype is the combination of alleles we have The alleles may be the same ( homozygous ) or different ( heterozygous ) forms of a gene and can be dominant or recessive in the way the gene is expressed as a characteristic, known as the phenotype . Autosomal Dominant An allele is described as autosomal dominant when only one copy is required to display the phenotype associated with the gene on an autosome . The associated phenotype will be present whether the individual is heterozygous or homozygous for the Autosomal Recessive An allele is described as autosomal recessive when two copies are required to display the phenotype associated with the gene on an autosome . The associated phenotype will be present only when the individual is homozygous for the Individuals who are heterozygous for the autosomal recessive allele are described as a carrier , they will not display the phenotype but can pass the allele onto their The X chromosome contains many genes, including those not related to sex While the Y chromosome does Therefore, genes on the X chromosome required by both sexes display a characteristic inheritance pattern described as , or Females, with two X chromosomes, have two copies of each gene and can therefore be heterozygous or homozygous for an Males, with one X and one Y chromosome, express all the alleles present on their only X chromosome (which they receive from their mother) and are described as hemizygous for that It’s all in the name – How variants are described If you have delved into the world of genetic testing, knowing your bases from your amino acids is pretty important in understanding what your results mean for your genetic code, especially when reading scientific Ready to dive in? Through a technique known as DNA sequencing, which determines the precise order of bases within the human genome, scientists now have a good idea of what the ‘common’ base is at each position, while most of t
